I can't believe most of the comments on this series. Don't people read the caption notes at all?? These shots are nearly 100 years old and from one of the greats of photography and especially Antarctic photography - Frank Hurley. Be amazed at his planning and endurance.  These were all shot on glass plates (about 4"x5") and would have been a nightmare to transport and weighed many hundreds of pounds. His camera weighed tens of pounds, and the wooden tripod likewise. Commenters that say LOL or ask questions of the photographer should pay more attention.
